---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Tenure | Governed context for AI agents"
  description="Tenure is the governance layer for AI memory: precise shared project state, scoped agent tokens, optional user persona context, provenance, and per-turn audit trails between every client, agent, and model."
>
  <main>

    <section id="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="hero-badge">
          <span class="hero-badge-dot"></span>
          No SDKs · Out-of-model Security · Zero Telemetry
        </div>


        <h1>The model does the thinking. </br> <span>Tenure</span> does the policing. </h1>


          <p class="hero-rag-line">Asking models to follow fragile system prompts is a losing battle.</p>

       

        <p class="hero-sub hero-sub-lede">

        Tenure gives every chat client, IDE, and agent precise context, turns observed agent behavior into deterministic policy, and blocks unsafe actions before they execute.


        </p>

        <div class="hero-cta-row">
          <a href="/how-it-works" class="btn-primary">See How It Works</a>
          <a href="/pricing" class="btn-secondary">View Pricing</a>
        </div>

         <div class="hero-stats">
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <span class="hero-stat-value">1.0<a href="https://huggingface.co/spaces/tenurehq/precisionmembench" style="color:var(--accent);font-size:0.7em;vertical-align:super;text-decoration:none">*</a></span>
            <span class="hero-stat-label">Retrieval precision</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <span class="hero-stat-value">&lt;15ms</span>
            <span class="hero-stat-label">latency</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <span class="hero-stat-value">0.00</span>
            <span class="hero-stat-label">Drift score</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <span class="hero-stat-value">0</span>
            <span class="hero-stat-label">SDK dependencies</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gateway-mock" aria-label="Example runtime decision made by Tenure">
          <div class="gateway-mock-bar">
            <span class="term-dot term-dot-red"></span>
            <span class="term-dot term-dot-yellow"></span>
            <span class="term-dot term-dot-green"></span>
            <span class="gateway-mock-title">RUNTIME GATEWAY <span class="gateway-mock-agent">agent:sales-outbound</span></span>
          </div>

          <div class="gateway-mock-body">
            <div class="gateway-mock-intent">
              <span class="gateway-mock-eyebrow">Agent Intent</span>
              <span class="gateway-mock-quote">&ldquo;Send follow-up offer to Prospect&rdquo;</span>
            </div>

            <div class="gateway-mock-eyebrow gateway-mock-eyebrow-checks">Evaluating preconditions&hellip;</div>

            <ul class="gateway-checks">
              <li class="gateway-check gateway-check-pass" style="--d:1">
                <span class="gateway-check-name">Identity <span class="gateway-check-dim">&mdash; Token authenticated, workload-id 9482</span></span>
                <span class="gateway-check-badge">PASS</span>
              </li>
              <li class="gateway-check gateway-check-pass" style="--d:2">
                <span class="gateway-check-name">Auth <span class="gateway-check-dim">&mdash; CRM write permission</span></span>
                <span class="gateway-check-badge">PASS</span>
              </li>
              <li class="gateway-check gateway-check-fail" style="--d:3">
                <span class="gateway-check-name">Precondition <span class="gateway-check-dim">&mdash; &ldquo;not currently a paying user&rdquo;</span></span>
                <span class="gateway-check-badge">FAIL</span>
                <span class="gateway-check-evidence">Evidence: CRM query returned &lsquo;active&rsquo;</span>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="gateway-decision" style="--d:4">
              <span class="gateway-decision-label">Decision</span>
              <span class="gateway-decision-value">Block &amp; escalate</span>
              <span class="gateway-decision-rule">Policy #104</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="state-vs-context">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">The problem</span>
        <h2>Your AI can act. Your infrastructure can't judge when it should.</h2>
        <p>
        AI is no longer trapped inside a chat bubble. Whether it's an internal copilot querying databases, a background agent updating a CRM, or a model executing tool calls, downstream business systems only check the API token. They are blind to whether the agent's actual intent is safe, authorized, or completely rogue.
        </p>

        <div class="problem-grid problem-grid-strong">
          <article class="problem-card">
            <span class="problem-number">01</span>
            <h3>Authenticated does not mean appropriate.</h3>
            <p>A valid token proves who is calling. It does not stop a customer-support bot from calling an internal deletion API.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="problem-card">
            <span class="problem-number">02</span>
            <h3>Permission does not equal intent.</h3>
            <p>An agent may have CRM access without being allowed to update every customer in every situation.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="problem-card">
            <span class="problem-number">03</span>
            <h3>Observability happens too late.</h3>
            <p>Logs will tell you how you got hacked. Enforcement stops it from happening.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>



    <section id="architecture" class="architecture-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Where Tenure fits</span>
        <h2>One gateway every agent request passes through.</h2>
        <p>
        Tenure intercepts agent activity at the runtime level. Every request is verified against active context and explicit policy: allowing, blocking, or escalating actions in under 15ms.
        </p>

        <div class="architecture-shell" aria-label="Tenure architecture diagram">
          <div class="architecture-row architecture-row-top">
            <div class="architecture-node client-node">Chat client</div>
            <div class="architecture-node client-node">IDE client</div>
            <div class="architecture-node client-node">Interactive agent</div>
            <div class="architecture-node client-node">Background agent</div>
          </div>

          <div class="architecture-arrow-row">
            <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
          </div>

          <div class="architecture-gateway">
            <span class="beta-badge">Private beta</span>
            <div class="architecture-gateway-header">
              <span class="architecture-kicker">Tenure</span>
              <h3>Runtime gateway</h3>
              <p>Every request gets eligible context. Every consequential action is checked before it executes.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="architecture-controls architecture-controls-simple">
              <div class="architecture-control">
                <strong>Identity</strong>
                <span>Every agent authenticates before it acts</span>
              </div>
              <div class="architecture-control">
                <strong>Permissions &amp; evidence</strong>
                <span>Checked against what the task actually requires</span>
              </div>
              <div class="architecture-control">
                <strong>Decision</strong>
                <span>Allow, block, or escalate, logged every time</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="architecture-arrow-row architecture-arrow-row-bottom">
            <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
          </div>

          <div class="architecture-row architecture-row-bottom-models">
            <div class="architecture-node model-node">Models</div>
            <div class="architecture-node model-node">Tools</div>
            <div class="architecture-node model-node">APIs</div>
            <div class="architecture-node model-node">Business Systems</div>
          </div>
        </div>
       
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="scoped-memory" class="section-surface">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Shared scoped memory</span>
        <h2>Shared memory without shared everything.</h2>
        <p class="section-lede">
          The memory lives in Tenure, not inside a single client. Tokens determine which context lanes are eligible for each
          agent or client, so shared state can travel across tools without collapsing every project, team, and user into one pool.
        </p>

        <div class="memory-visual">
          <div class="memory-scope-stack">
            <div class="memory-scope scope-org">
              <span class="scope-kind">ORG</span>
              <strong>Never send customer secrets to third-party tools.</strong>
              <small>Absolute organizational rule</small>
            </div>
            <div class="memory-scope scope-team">
              <span class="scope-kind">TEAM</span>
              <strong>Platform APIs use structured error envelopes.</strong>
              <small>Shared team practice</small>
            </div>
            <div class="memory-scope scope-project">
              <span class="scope-kind">PROJECT</span>
              <strong>Payments service migration targets PostgreSQL 18.</strong>
              <small>Project-specific state</small>
            </div>
            <div class="memory-scope scope-user muted-scope">
              <span class="scope-kind">USER</span>
              <strong>Prefer concise explanations with code first.</strong>
              <small>Persona lane · not eligible for this token</small>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="memory-token-card">
            <div class="memory-token-header">
              <span>Token policy</span>
              <strong>agent:code-reviewer</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="token-policy-row"><span>Org context</span><b class="policy-on">Allowed</b></div>
            <div class="token-policy-row"><span>Team: platform</span><b class="policy-on">Allowed</b></div>
            <div class="token-policy-row"><span>Project: payments</span><b class="policy-on">Allowed</b></div>
            <div class="token-policy-row"><span>User persona</span><b class="policy-off">Off</b></div>
            <div class="token-policy-divider"></div>
            <div class="token-output">
              <span class="token-output-label">Eligible context</span>
              <strong>3 scoped beliefs</strong>
              <small>Only active, relevant state can enter the request.</small>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="three-pillars">
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-label">Structured Beliefs over Vector Dumps</div>
            <p>Drop the loose conversation history. Tenure maps relations, entities, and open questions into precise, queryable state.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-label">Cryptographic Isolation</div>
            <p>Multi-tenant project and team isolation are structural. Agents only inherit user personas when explicitly allowed by the token.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-label">Tamper-Proof Audit Trails</div>
            <p>Every single belief retains its origin, scope, and lifecycle history. Know exactly why an agent knew something, and when it found out.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="precision" class="section-surface">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Memory precision</span>
        <h2>Deterministic memory injection. Zero prompt bloat.</h2>
        <p class="section-lede">
         Tenure retrieves scoped belief state precisely, outperforming standard vector strategies by up to 4x on standard agent benchmarks without adding latency.
        </p>

        <div class="precision-proof">
          <div class="precision-chart">
            <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label tenure-label">Tenure</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill tenure-fill"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value tenure-val">1.00</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label">Open Knowledge Format</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill comparison-fill" style="width:47%"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value other-val">0.47</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label">Supermemory</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill comparison-fill" style="width:22%"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value other-val">0.22</span>
            </div>
             <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label">gbrain</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill comparison-fill" style="width:14%"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value other-val">0.14</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label">Zep</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill comparison-fill" style="width:9%"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value other-val">0.09</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label">Mem0</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill comparison-fill" style="width:6%"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value other-val">0.06</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bar-row">
              <span class="bar-label">Hindsight</span>
              <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill comparison-fill" style="width:6%"></div></div>
              <span class="bar-value other-val">0.06</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="precision-stat-stack">
            <div class="precision-stat">
              <strong>89</strong>
              <span>benchmark cases</span>
            </div>
            <div class="precision-stat">
              <strong>&lt;15ms</strong>
              <span>context injection</span>
            </div>
            <div class="precision-stat">
              <strong>0.00</strong>
              <span>drift score</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="proof-links">
          <a href="/benchmark">Explore PrecisionMemBench →</a>
          <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.11325">Read the memory paper →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="visibility">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="label">Built to be inspected</span>
        <h2>Nothing important should be invisible.</h2>
        <p class="section-lede">
          Tenure records the state it stores, the context it injects, and the decisions it makes. Stop reconstructing execution chains after a failure occurs. Track every state shift, context injection, and runtime block in real-time.
        </p>

        <div class="visibility-grid">
          <article class="audit-window">
            <div class="audit-window-bar">
              <span>MEMORY RECORD</span>
              <b>belief:v12</b>
            </div>
            <div class="audit-window-body">
              <span class="audit-field">TYPE <b>decision</b></span>
              <span class="audit-field">SCOPE <b>project:payments</b></span>
              <p>&ldquo;Payments migration targets PostgreSQL 18.&rdquo;</p>
              <div class="audit-meta">source: session_482 · supersedes: belief:v11</div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="audit-window">
            <div class="audit-window-bar">
              <span>INJECTION LOG</span>
              <b>turn:1842</b>
            </div>
            <div class="audit-window-body">
              <span class="audit-field">TOKEN <b>agent:code-reviewer</b></span>
              <span class="audit-field">ELIGIBLE <b>3 beliefs</b></span>
              <p>Injected project decision + team API practice.</p>
              <div class="audit-meta">user persona excluded by token policy</div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="audit-window">
            <div class="audit-window-bar">
              <span>RUNTIME DECISION</span>
              <b class="audit-red">BLOCK</b>
            </div>
            <div class="audit-window-body">
              <span class="audit-field">POLICY <b>#104 · v7</b></span>
              <span class="audit-field">EVIDENCE <b>active_account=true</b></span>
              <p>Follow-up offer blocked before CRM action executed.</p>
              <div class="audit-meta">decision and evidence recorded at runtime</div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>



    <section id="cta">
      <div class="container cta-card">
        <span class="label">Get started</span>
        <h2>Secure and contextualize every AI request at runtime.</h2>
        <p class="cta-sub">Run Tenure Community to give shared context to your AI tools, or leverage Pro to govern every outbound LLM call across your entire company.</p>

        <div class="hero-cta-row">
         <a href="/pricing" class="btn-primary">View Pricing</a>
 <a href="/docs/quickstart" class="btn-secondary">Get Started</a>        
 </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <style>
    .hero-sub-lede {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .hero-stats-secondary {
      margin-top: 1.4rem;
    }

    .gateway-mock {
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 1.6rem 0 0;
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--border2, #2a2a2a);
      background: var(--surface, #111111);
      box-shadow: 0 24px 60px -30px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
      font-family: var(--mono);
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-top: 6rem;
      margin-right: auto;
    }

    .gateway-mock-bar {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
      background: var(--surface2, #1a1a1a);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border, #222222);
    }

    .gateway-mock-title {
      margin-left: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      color: var(--muted, #b8b8b8);
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .gateway-mock-agent {
      color: var(--accent, #00a8ad);
    }

    .gateway-mock-body {
      padding: 1rem 1.1rem 1.15rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .gateway-mock-intent {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.2rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
    }

    .gateway-mock-eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.65rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--dim, #7a7a7a);
    }

    .gateway-mock-eyebrow-checks {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .gateway-mock-quote {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text, #e8e8e8);
    }

    .gateway-checks {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
      padding: 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.4rem;
    }

    .gateway-check {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.3rem 0.6rem;
      padding: 0.45rem 0.6rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border, #222222);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
      font-size: 0.76rem;
      opacity: 0;
      animation: gatewayReveal 0.4s ease forwards;
      animation-delay: calc(var(--d) * 0.35s);
    }

    .gateway-check-name {
      flex: 1 1 auto;
      color: var(--text, #e8e8e8);
    }

    .gateway-check-dim {
      color: var(--dim, #7a7a7a);
    }

    .gateway-check-badge {
      font-weight: 800;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
    }

    .gateway-check-pass {
      border-color: rgba(34,197,94,0.25);
    }

    .gateway-check-pass .gateway-check-badge {
      color: var(--green, #22c55e);
      background: rgba(34,197,94,0.12);
      border: 1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);
    }

    .gateway-check-fail {
      border-color: rgba(196,83,83,0.35);
      background: rgba(196,83,83,0.06);
    }

    .gateway-check-fail .gateway-check-badge {
      color: var(--red, #c45353);
      background: rgba(196,83,83,0.14);
      border: 1px solid rgba(196,83,83,0.35);
    }

    .gateway-check-evidence {
      flex-basis: 100%;
      color: var(--red, #c45353);
      opacity: 0.85;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    .gateway-decision {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.6rem 0.7rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(196,83,83,0.4);
      background: rgba(196,83,83,0.1);
      opacity: 0;
      animation: gatewayReveal 0.4s ease forwards;
      animation-delay: calc(var(--d) * 0.35s);
    }

    .gateway-decision-label {
      font-size: 0.65rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--dim, #7a7a7a);
    }

    .gateway-decision-value {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--red, #c45353);
    }

    .gateway-decision-rule {
      margin-left: auto;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      color: var(--dim, #7a7a7a);
    }

    @keyframes gatewayReveal {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .gateway-mock-body {
        padding: 0.85rem 0.8rem 1rem;
      }

      .gateway-decision-rule {
        margin-left: 0;
      }
    }

    .architecture-section {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .architecture-shell {
      max-width: 660px;
      margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
      padding: 0.85rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 168, 173, 0.22);
      border-radius: 20px;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(0, 168, 173, 0.18), transparent 34%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.045), rgba(255,255,255,0.015));
    }

    .architecture-row {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.45rem;
    }

    .architecture-row-top {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .architecture-row-bottom-models {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .groundeval-strip {
      max-width: 660px;
      margin: 1.25rem auto 0;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.8rem;
      border: 1px dashed rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.4);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.05);
    }

    .groundeval-label {
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
    }

    .groundeval-kicker {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--violet, #a29bfe);
      padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.35);
      background: rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.14);
    }

    .groundeval-caption {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--dim, #7a7a7a);
    }

    .groundeval-steps {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .groundeval-step {
      padding: 0.45rem 0.55rem;
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: var(--violet, #6c5ce7);
      border: 1px solid rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.5);
      text-align: center;
    }

    .groundeval-step strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.74rem;
      color: #ffffff;
      margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
    }

    .groundeval-step span {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.64rem;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78);
    }

    .groundeval-arrow {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .groundeval-connector {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  margin: 0.15rem 0;
}

.groundeval-connector-line {
  position: relative;
  width: 1px;
  height: 20px;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(108,92,231,0.15), rgba(108,92,231,0.9));
}

.groundeval-connector-line::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  left: -4px;
  top: 12px;
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
  border-right: 1px solid rgba(108,92,231,0.9);
